<div class="container">
  <div class="row valign-wrapper">
    <div class="col s8 center-align">
      <img class="homepage-screenshot" src="images/graph.png" alt="Overview Screenshot">
    </div>
    <div class="col s4 valign">
      <h5>Visually Track Progress</h5>

      <p>
        Using a simple but effective line chart you can easily see where you currently are in relation to your used car mileage, compared with the estimated usage based settings you provide.
      </p>
   </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row valign-wrapper">
    <div class="col s4 valign">
      <h5>Find Exact Remaining Usage</h5>

      <p>
        With mileager's monthly view you can get the exact percentage of the mileage you have have remaining on a month-by-month basis. Mileager calculates your monthly mileage allowance and works calculates the percentage used using data from your inputted mileage recordings.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col s8 center-align">
      <img class="homepage-screenshot_monthly" src="images/monthly.png" alt="Overview Screenshot">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row valign-wrapper">
    <div class="col s8 center-align">
      <img class="homepage-screenshot" src="images/settings.png" alt="Overview Screenshot">
    </div>
    <div class="col s4 valign">
      <h5>Customize It To You</h5>

      <p>
        From initial set up Car Mileager asks you to set your settings to fit your needs, from the term length of your cars contract to the starting mileage, you have total control over calculations.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col s12 center-align">
      <h5>We're Open Source...</h5>
      <p>
        Mileager is entirely an open source project with it's source code hosted on GitHub. Written in Ruby on Rails as well as utilizing other various other CSS, Javascript and Ruby libraries.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/allistera/car_mileager_front">
      <img src="images/octocat.png" alt="Find us on Github" width="100">
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
